### 21.

1\. Now at that time edible fruit was very plentiful in Sâvatthi, but
there was no one to make it allowable <span
id="fr_178"></span>[2](#fn_176.md). And the Bhikkhus, fearing to offend,
would not eat of it.

They told that thing to the Blessed One.

'I allow you, O Bhikkhus, to eat fruit which has not yet had any seed in
it, or which has no more seed in it, even without any one being there to
make it allowable <span id="fr_179"></span>[3](#fn_177.md).'

